Generate Synthetic Ecological Data

Source: R/synthetic.R
ei_synthetic.Rd

Samples data from the following truncated Normal ecological model: $$ x_i \stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim} \mathrm{Dirichlet}(\alpha) \\ b_i \stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim} \mathcal{N}_{[0, 1]^d}(\eta, \Sigma) \\ y_i = b_i^\top x_i, $$ where \(\alpha\) is a vector of hyperparameters that may be optionally specified as the x argument to the function, and \(\mathcal{N}_{[0, 1]^d}\) indicates a multivariate Normal distribution truncated to the d-dimensional hypercube.

Usage

ei_synthetic(
  x = c(3, 1),
  eta = seq(0.5, 0.9, length.out = ncol(x) %||% length(x)),
  Sigma = 0.02 * (1 + diag(ncol(x) %||% length(x))),
  n = nrow(x)
)

Arguments

x

Either a matrix or data frame containing the predictor percentages in each row, or a vector containing Dirichlet parameters to use in sampling predictor percentages.

eta

The center of the distribution of geography-level parameters. Defaults to a sequence across groups.

Sigma

The covariance matrix for geography-level parameters.

n

The number of rows (geographies) to generate. Defaults to the number of rows in x, if the latter is a matrix or data frame.

Value

A list with elements x (predictors), y (outcome), b (geography-level parameters), and eta and Sigma (global parameters).
